<paragraph blockId="5.[192,802,1472,1863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis box="[192,300,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Total length of the examined male 34.4 mm. Fingers of pedipalps flexed proximally. Movable finger of pedipalp bears 11 rows of granules, all without external and with internal granules. Trichobothria 
<emphasis box="[730,757,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">db</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[192,222,1594,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">est</emphasis>
situated next to each other, approximately equidistant from 
<emphasis box="[262,298,1625,1648]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">esb</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[372,397,1625,1648]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">eb</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[423,498,1625,1648]" captionStart="Figures 1–2" captionStartId="3.[875,961,1083,1106]" captionTargetBox="[211,808,183,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[192,851,168,1199]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1–2: Chela of pedipalp showing external trichobothria. 1. Sassanidotus zarudnyi (Birula, 1900), male neotype. 2. Sassanidotus gracilis (Birula, 1900), female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648995/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Intermediate carinae of metasomal segment II may reach three-quarters of segment length; metasomal segment III bears in place of intermediate carinae only about 10 posteriorly situated irregular granules; metasomal segment IV with lateral surface sparsely covered by granules that do not form rows or carinae. Tarsomere I of legs I to III with bristlecombs. Pectinal teeth number 22. Telson bulbous.
</paragraph>
