(Birula, 1900a: 11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[830,1441,705,1127]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis box="[830,943,705,728]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Comments</emphasis>
: The 
<typeStatus box="[1018,1111,705,728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1189,1279,705,728]" country="Iran" name="Tehran" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Teheran</collectingRegion>
, published by Birula (1900a), is absent from the collection of the Zoological Museum of 
<collectingRegion box="[1086,1238,766,789]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Moscow State</collectingRegion>
University (K. M. Mikhailov, pers. comm., 
<date box="[1109,1230,797,820]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" value="2006-04">April 2006</date>
), and therefore we consider it to be lost. The record and brief description of the male specimen from Seistan, which we examined, was published by the same author later (Birula, 1903: 70). Birula (1903) noted that there were no diagnostic differences (even at the level of subspecies) between the 
<collectingRegion box="[831,917,981,1004]" country="Iran" name="Tehran" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Teheran</collectingRegion>
and Seistan males. Following Article 75 of the Code (ICZN, 1999), we designate here the Seistan male (
<collectionCode box="[839,894,1042,1065]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">ZISP</collectionCode>
599) as a 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1123,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<typeStatus box="[1038,1123,1042,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">neotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. At the same time, Birula described 
